# Auth Rules

- Keep JWT parse and user-shape logic in a single source (`useJwtToken` or a shared util).
- Reuse `useRefreshToken` and shared token checks; do not introduce parallel refresh flows.
- Avoid ad-hoc redirects; use existing routing and auth flow patterns.
- Do not add direct cookie mutations outside established auth utilities unless necessary.
- When changing auth behavior, include failure-path handling (expired, invalid, or missing token).
